                            <comment id="279075" author="adilger" created="Wed, 9 Sep 2020 00:22:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Dongyang, I see &lt;a href=&quot;#comment-263035&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;comment-263035&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;#comment-276924&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;comment-276924&lt;/a&gt; report failures for SLES 4.&lt;b&gt;12&lt;/b&gt;.14 kernels, but the patch skips kernels 4.&lt;b&gt;14&lt;/b&gt; and later.  Is that a typo in the patch?  Should this test be skipped for kernels &amp;gt;= 4.12 instead?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
