&lt;p&gt;It can be reproduced on 4.14+ without lustre, so again it is a kernel problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="260923" author="adilger" created="Thu, 9 Jan 2020 19:54:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/32265&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/32265&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4398&quot; title=&quot;mdt_object_open_lock() may not flush conflicting handles&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4398&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4398&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; llite: do not cache write open lock for exec file&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; was landed as 2.12.56-76-g6dd9d57bc0, which was just before the 2.12.58 build that this was first reported on, so there is likely a connection.  I would have thought the 32265 patch would &lt;b&gt;fix&lt;/b&gt; this problem, but maybe it only became evident for the newer kernels because sanity test_817 was re-enabled by that patch?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="259933" author="gerrit" created="Mon, 16 Dec 2019 05:59:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oleg Drokin (green@whamcloud.com) merged in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/36712/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/36712/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
